Two men yesterday appeared before a Badagry Chief Magistrates’ Court for allegedly stealing N419,000. The court granted them N500,000 bail. Chief Magistrate Patrick Adekomaya ordered the accused – Ahmefula John, 45, and Emmanuel Mike, 42, to produce two sureties in the like sum. The prosecutor, Akpan Ikem, said the accused on July 26 stole the money belonging to Alhaji Kawume at Ovuru Street, Okokomaiko. “The two men were caught and handed over to the police while trying to run away after stealing the money,” the prosecutor said. The accused pleaded not guilty. The case continues on September 5.